<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Booh</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-24 09:26:27</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well, I finally got my glacier cloak.  I am lvl 30.  One good hint is the<BR>
Glacier Bear resisted my Frost Strike a few times.  (Frost Strike was never successful.)<BR>
I guess he has good tolerance for the cold stuff ;-)  He conned Blue to me at 30.<BR>
<BR>
If you learn the path of the lich it is not that bad.  When I zone in I go to the right and work my way around.<BR>
That way I go in the same direction as the lich.  The lich only killed me once and that was when <BR>
I mistook him for an Ice Bone and walked right up to him.  (OUCH!)<BR>
<BR>
Sense animal is VERY useful in tracking the Glacier Bear.  If you go in just a bit to the middle part of zone you can<BR>
"sense animals" and he be highlighted as your target.  <BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Rhuargh of M Marr</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-31 08:17:13</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I recently turned 35 shaman and decide to get myself a new headpiece so I prepared myself for a long and boring time of my life. After locating the hole in the ice I dove into the hole and swam into the cave, approached carefully keeping my head up for the lich. After running around for 30 minutes or so I came to the conclusion that it was empty, no lich, no PHs and no bear. Checked my watch and decided to come back couple of hours later, my next try several hours later resulted in 2 dead PHs and a big scare by the lich. Reseted the timer and prepared myself for the 8 hour long wait. After about 8 hours I went back with my hopes high and ran in used sense animal only got stupid snow leopard on target. Proceeded further in and almost ran into the lich again and found one PH, killed and started to cast sense animal again, but before the spell went off, the bear came walking straight for me and my heart almost raced, and my fingers started to tremble, here he was.<BR>
Killed him easy with root and a few dots, was blue to me.<BR>
Can't believe the luck I had :).<BR>
<BR>
For the second part of the quest I went to cazic thule and got into a tae-group and spent 4-5 hours there before finally one lizard page dropped one ogreskin chamois.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Rhuargh of Mith Marr</font></td></tr></table>
