<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Adarkar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-16 20:28:25</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Sigh,<BR>
Ok guys here is some more info for you to feast on.<BR>
There are several IMPORTANT points not even mentioned in <BR>
the other posts.<BR>
<BR>
NUMBER ONE!  the Glacier bear pelt is EXTRA large. that means it will not fit in most regular bags<BR>
You should loot it with a right click and put it into an open PRIMARY inventory slot, otherwise you will lose the item.<BR>
I was told by one of the main GMs on Bertox (Tinysa) that I was SCREWED.<BR>
20 friggin hours of camping and I had nothing to show for it.<BR>
Anyhow, don't get stuck by this bug, IMHO it should fall back on the body if you do not have a large enough spot for the item or it should be made LARGE instead of extra large<BR>
I tried the mammoth Rib bone and it does the same thing, it goes away if you do not have a tinker's bag or open PRIMARY inventory slot open.<BR>
Not a big deal as the rib bones are a dime a dozen.<BR>
<BR>
NUMBER TWO!  Camp your character either in the ice cave or close to it the night before a patch or other server outage.<BR>
Thats right, you still have a chance for the placeholder but you don't have to wait 6 to 8 hours to find out!<BR>
I got one pelt the night before a patch while moving my character to the cave and one the very next morning ( I had to loot it with my wife's level 20 character LOL)<BR>
upon system startup.<BR>
You will spend your time more productive but it might take you  a month or two to get your helm, but with the lich down there now, you can not just log on down there and leave for a couple hours like you used to to hold the camp.<BR>
<BR>
The page does not always drop the skin, just get into a tae group and you might get you a lizzy mantle or cloak while you wait.<BR>
<BR>
If someone you know gets the Glacier Bear pelt and does not want the helm (IE a cleric that got the icon) you can get all the other items and turn them in together in Lake rathe to still get your helm.<BR>
<BR>
The pelt dropped everytime I killed the bear, but I only saw the icon one time.<BR>
<BR>
Good hunting<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
